pageContext.claim: “China has agreed to buy massive amounts of ADDITIONAL Farm/Agricultural Products - would be one of the best things to happen to our farmers in many years!”
pageContext.analysis: The exact amount of agricultural products that China has agreed to buy has not been announced. The soybean saga came about after China retaliated to Trump's threats of tariffs by cancelling a long-standing trade deal to import American soybeans. It's not clear if the proposed new deal would benefit farmers.
